We will have a great time.... Once you are here...You are family!

If you fly into Newark Airport (EWR) and staying at least 7 days,  Book an UBER or Lyft taxi and send photo of bill for refund (Up to $10).

Thanks!!!

neighborhood_overview:
Newark is a city on the rise! The apartment is located in the historic Lincoln Park neighborhood of downtown Newark. A five minute drive will take you to and from the airport or Jersey Gardens Outlet Mall. You can walk a few blocks to downtown shops like Nike or grab a bite to eat at local restaurants, or jump on public transport to New York City, Atlantic City or Philly. Entertainment venues nearby are the Prudential Center, home of the Jersey Devils Hockey team and NJPAC ( New Jersey Performing Arts Center.

Lincoln Park has been nicknamed the "Arts District" of Newark. Lincoln Park is home to the City Without Walls art gallery; the Newark School of the Arts and Newark Symphony Hall, a venue for hip-hop, rap, jazz, and performing arts events and concerts. Lincoln Park is a block away from the apartment. You can walk, ride or bike to local restaurants. A few of my favorites Marcus B &P on Halsey street, Mercato Tomato Pie on Market Street, Chateau of Spain on Hill Street a
host_about: I am single and like to mingle. I love to laugh and enjoy life. I love to travel and have been to  a few foreign countries ( Brazil, Greece, England, France, China, Canada, Mexico)  and many of the Caribbean islands (Aruba, Bermuda, Bahamas, Dominican Republic, Jamaica, Puerto Rico, St. Martin, Barbados, US Virgin Islands) and Hawaii. My favorite travel destination was the beautiful island of Oahu, Hawaii.  My favorite activities are of course traveling, reading non-fiction books, eating great home-cooked food, going to a concert to hear good live music, dance or drama and watching  movies on the big screen.  My motto: Seize the Day and Count Your Blessings!

We are in the Lower Broadway neighborhood just north of Downtown Newark which is home to a diverse population of Latinos and immigrants from other backgrounds. This means that great food, access to public transportation, shows and many other great perks are within walking distance.

This is a vibrant neighborhood that, like other key areas of Newark, is going through significant renewal and redevelopment, processes that are still very much under way (i.e., we are not as beautiful as we will soon be). If you don't let yourself be stopped by the couple of lots waiting redevelopment around us, you will find an array of small family-run restaurants and stores within 1-2 blocks radius of the apartment. Still, while luxury condos have begun to pop up here and there, we feel safe, and we think our neighbors are among the best, the Lower Broadway still remains much

Hi  This is Mario!

We have an excellent support team for great stays  and nice places!

I'm giving you $5 off each of your first 4 Uber rides. To accept, use code 'marioc2038ue' to sign up. Enjoy! Details:  uber site  and  invite  and marioc2038ue

Limon and Costa Rica are very friendly places.  So, is Irvington, NJ, USA.

We love to provide excellent service and to excel in everything we do.

If we please you, tell many friends...If we miss our goal, please tell me..
:)  :)  :)

 I love to make new friends, good food, to explore new places and have fun.    
Please contact me if you are planning to explore NYC, NJ,  or Costa Rica.
 
We will have a great time.... Once you are here...You are family!

If you fly into Newark Airport (EWR) and staying at least 7 days,  Book an UBER or Lyft taxi and send photo of bill for refund (Up to $10).   

Also, I love to ski ...Poconos Skiing resort is 50 minutes away.  You can learn  to Ski ,Snowboard, or just slide down the slopes here!!!

Thanks!!!

neighborhood_overview:
Gentrification is the better way to describe Newark in one word. For many years Newark has been going through this process, but things seem to have picked up at much faster pace in the last few years. Big organizations such as Whole Foods, Barnes & Noble, Starbucks, Nike and many others have noticed something in Newark when they decided to open shop here, now it’s your turn to come and see it.

My spot is located in the IRONBOUND section of Newark, and according to Neighborhood Scout, the IRONBOUND is Newark’s SAFEST neighborhood. Additional to being the safest, it offers the broadest culinary diversity in the area with many restaurants offering the best Spanish Paella, Portuguese seafood, Brazilian Churrasco, and many others.

Guests who are staying in, can take advantage of all the restaurants and bars that are popping up throughout the city while staying in a comfortable place that is close to pretty much everything.

host_about:
Hi  This is Mario!    

Look no further... 
We have an excellent support team for great stays  and nice places! 
We add new things  weekly...

I made it from NYC (Port Authority 8th Ave and 42 Street to Irvington with bus # 107X in 20 minutes when there is little traffic. 

Also,  We provide excellent WiFi and 2 WIFI networks at each house.

You may want to try downloading ROKU app for use on our Roku smart TVs.

We use door codes.  No keys needs.
We change codes after each guest leaves.

I'm giving you $5 off each of your first 4 Uber rides. To accept, use code 'marioc2038ue' to sign up. Enjoy! Details:  uber site  and  invite  and marioc2038ue

I'm originally from Costa Rica.   My Grand parents moved from Jamaica to  Limon, Costa Rica to work on building a railroad  to San Jose 100 years ago.
Limon and Costa Rica are very friendly places.  So, is Irvington, NJ, USA.

We love to provide excellent service and to excel in everything we do.

If we please you, tell many friends...If we miss our goal, please tell me..
:)  :)  :)

 I love to make new friends, good food, to explore new places and have fun.    
Please contact me if you are planning to explore NYC, NJ,  or Costa Rica.
 
We will have a great time.... Once you are here...You are family!

If you fly into Newark Airport (EWR) and staying at least 7 days,  Book an UBER or Lyft taxi and send photo of bill for refund (Up to $10).

Thanks!!!

neighborhood_overview: Quiet street conveniently located 5 minutes from Newark Liberty International Airport. 10 minutes from Downtown Newark and Jersey Gardens Outlet Mall. 15-20 from other neighboring malls and stadiums (Short Hills, American Dream, Meadowlands arenas). host_about: Hi, my name is  Patrick Mamudu. I am co-hosting this humble abode with my mother, Catherine Luke.  We have lived in the Southward section of Newark, NJ since the early '80s.  Our current interests are traveling, shopping, teaching (in various public high schools in the city of Newark, New Jersey), cooking, attending church every Sunday, Tuesday, and Wednesday, STEM (science, technology, engineering, and math), movies, music, and medicine.  Our ethnic origin is Nigeria, and we take pride in our culture. We love wearing our native culture clothes and also cooking many of the staple dishes from there (jollof rice, fried rice, moi moi, akara, suya, pounded yam, etc). A fun fact about Catherine is that she has been to several European countries during the '90s in order to sell many of the native clothing that is a staple in our country. I have been to London, Italy, Belgium, Switzerland, Germany, Spain, France, Austria,  etc.  We are devout Christians and believe that God is the centerpiece of our life; he has been good to us.  Our faith allows us to be hospitable hosts who value all of our guests. We take the extra step in making sure your stay is comfortable and feels just like home. We are also helpful in regards to movement within the Greater New York region.

neighborhood_overview:
Gentrification is the better way to describe Newark in one word. For many years Newark has been going through this process, but things seem to have picked up at much faster pace in the last few years. Big organizations such as Whole Foods, Barnes & Noble, Starbucks, Nike and many others have noticed something in Newark when they decided to open shop here, now it’s your turn to come and see it.

My spot is located in the IRONBOUND section of Newark, and according to Neighborhood Scout, the IRONBOUND is Newark’s SAFEST neighborhood. Additional to being the safest, it offers the broadest culinary diversity in the area with many restaurants offering the best Spanish Paella, Portuguese seafood, Brazilian Churrasco, and many others.

Guests who are staying in, can take advantage of all the restaurants and bars that are popping up throughout the city while staying in a comfortable place that is close to pretty much everything.

host_about: Hi, my name is  Patrick Mamudu. I am co-hosting this humble abode with my mother, Catherine Luke.  We have lived in the Southward section of Newark, NJ since the early '80s.  Our current interests are traveling, shopping, teaching (in various public high schools in the city of Newark, New Jersey), cooking, attending church every Sunday, Tuesday, and Wednesday, STEM (science, technology, engineering, and math), movies, music, and medicine.  Our ethnic origin is Nigeria, and we take pride in our culture. We love wearing our native culture clothes and also cooking many of the staple dishes from there (jollof rice, fried rice, moi moi, akara, suya, pounded yam, etc). A fun fact about Catherine is that she has been to several European countries during the '90s in order to sell many of the native clothing that is a staple in our country. I have been to London, Italy, Belgium, Switzerland, Germany, Spain, France, Austria,  etc.  We are devout Christians and believe that God is the centerpiece of our life; he has been good to us.  Our faith allows us to be hospitable hosts who value all of our guests. We take the extra step in making sure your stay is comfortable and feels just like home. We are also helpful in regards to movement within the Greater New York region.

host_about:
Hi  This is Mario!    

Look no further... 
We have an excellent support team for great stays  and nice places! 
We add new things  weekly...

I made it from NYC (Port Authority 8th Ave and 42 Street to Irvington with bus # 107X in 20 minutes when there is little traffic. 

Also,  We provide excellent WiFi and 2 WIFI networks at each house.

You may want to try downloading ROKU app for use on our Roku smart TVs.

We use door codes.  No keys needs.
We change codes after each guest leaves.

I'm giving you $5 off each of your first 4 Uber rides. To accept, use code 'marioc2038ue' to sign up. Enjoy! Details:  uber site  and  invite  and marioc2038ue

I'm originally from Costa Rica.   My Grand parents moved from Jamaica to  Limon, Costa Rica to work on building a railroad  to San Jose 100 years ago.
Limon and Costa Rica are very friendly places.  So, is Irvington, NJ, USA.

We love to provide excellent service and to excel in everything we do.

If we please you, tell many friends...If we miss our goal, please tell me..
:)  :)  :)

 I love to make new friends, good food, to explore new places and have fun.    
Please contact me if you are planning to explore NYC, NJ,  or Costa Rica.
 
We will have a great time.... Once you are here...You are family!

If you fly into Newark Airport (EWR) and staying at least 7 days,  Book an UBER or Lyft taxi and send photo of bill for refund (Up to $10).   

Also, I love to ski ...Poconos Skiing resort is 50 minutes away.  You can learn  to Ski ,Snowboard, or just slide down the slopes here!!!

Thanks!!!

Hi  This is Mario!

We have an excellent support team for great stays  and nice places! 
We add new things  weekly...

Limon and Costa Rica are very friendly places.  So, is Irvington, NJ, USA.

We love to provide excellent service and to excel in everything we do.

If we please you, tell many friends...If we miss our goal, please tell me..
:)  :)  :)

 I love to make new friends, good food, to explore new places and have fun.    
Please contact me if you are planning to explore NYC, NJ,  or Costa Rica.
 
We will have a great time.... Once you are here...You are family!

If you fly into Newark Airport (EWR) and staying at least 7 days,  Book an UBER or Lyft taxi and send photo of bill for refund (Up to $10).

Thanks!!!

neighborhood_overview: Ironbound is a neighborhood in the city of Newark in Essex County, New Jersey, United States. It is a largely working-class, close-knit, multi-ethnic community covering approximately four square miles (10 km²). Historically, the area was called "Dutch Neck," "Down Neck," or simply "the Neck," due to the appearance of the curve of the Passaic River. The Ironbound is part of Newark's East Ward and is directly east of Newark Penn Station and Downtown Newark, and south and west of the river, over which passes the Jackson Street Bridge, connecting to Harrison and Kearny.

We offer you the best service, amenities and environment!

name: Townhouse in Newark · ★4.87 · 1 bedroom · 1 bed · 1.5 shared baths
description:
The house is located in the University Heights section of Newark and is very close to the Newark airport, Rutgers, NJIT and Essex County College. The location is safe with free street parking or a guest 24 hour parking pass can be obtained from security. Whole Foods and Starbucks are downtown or ShopRite can be walked to. Some restaurants are nearby and more options are downtown or in the historic Ironbound section. The house is located steps away from public transportation to Manhattan.

The space
The house has three bedrooms and two and a half bathrooms. The room for guests is spacious with a queen bed (a cot is also available for larger groups) large closet, dresser, desk, TV (Roku stick with Netflix and Hulu) and two windows which let in a lot of natural light when the blackout curtains are drawn.

I live in the master bathroom and have my own full bathroom. The full bathroom in the hallway is shared with only my tenant who occupies the third room.
neighborhood_overview: University Heights is being called the new Brooklyn. The Renaissance of Newark is underway with new restaurants and apartment buildings. The house is located in the heart of where the action is but far enough away from downtown to mimic suburbia. You can enjoy a nice day in the Veterans Memorial Park or head downtown to try out the chic restaurants on Halsey Street. Go see a show at NJPAC or catch a Devils game at the Prudential Center. You also don't want to miss an opportunity to eat at a Brazilian restaurant in the Ironbound section.
host_about: I'm originally from Delaware and have been living in Newark since 2011. I was brought to the area by my desire to work in the media industry (I also didn't mind trading in sleepy Delaware for New York City). I can't live without a good movie (The Graduate is my favorite), music, my faith, my dog Mama and Zumba class.

neighborhood_overview: Ironbound is a neighborhood in the city of Newark in Essex County, New Jersey, United States. It is a largely working-class, close-knit, multi-ethnic community covering approximately four square miles (10 km²). Historically, the area was called "Dutch Neck," "Down Neck," or simply "the Neck," due to the appearance of the curve of the Passaic River. The Ironbound is part of Newark's East Ward and is directly east of Newark Penn Station and Downtown Newark, and south and west of the river, over which passes the Jackson Street Bridge, connecting to Harrison and Kearny.

neighborhood_overview:
A quiet neighborhood nestled against the first county park in the United States, it is minutes to a night at the symphony at Newark's NJPAC, a concert or hockey game at the Prudential Center, an art opening at one of Newark’s many galleries, and dinner and drinks downtown. Forest Hill Newark is the perfect escape for quiet evenings at home while offering access to everything the region has to offer. Just 3 short blocks from the apartment is Branch Book Park, the cherry blossom capital of the US, there are more than 5,000 cherry blossom trees – even more than in Washington, DC! The park has vast open spaces and offers many recreational facilities including ball fields, a 20-court tennis complex, an indoor roller-skating rink, new children’s playgrounds and a visitor center.

Forest Hill Newark must be experienced to be believed!

Hi  This is Mario!    

Look no further... 
We have an excellent support team for great stays  and nice places! 
We add new things  weekly...

I made it from NYC (Port Authority 8th Ave and 42 Street to Irvington with bus # 107X in 20 minutes when there is little traffic. 

Also,  We provide excellent WiFi and 2 WIFI networks at each house.

You may want to try downloading ROKU app for use on our Roku smart TVs.

We use door codes.  No keys needs.
We change codes after each guest leaves.

I'm giving you $5 off each of your first 4 Uber rides. To accept, use code 'marioc2038ue' to sign up. Enjoy! Details:  uber site  and  invite  and marioc2038ue

I'm originally from Costa Rica.   My Grand parents moved from Jamaica to  Limon, Costa Rica to work on building a railroad  to San Jose 100 years ago.
Limon and Costa Rica are very friendly places.  So, is Irvington, NJ, USA.

We love to provide excellent service and to excel in everything we do.

If we please you, tell many friends...If we miss our goal, please tell me..
:)  :)  :)

 I love to make new friends, good food, to explore new places and have fun.    
Please contact me if you are planning to explore NYC, NJ,  or Costa Rica.
 
We will have a great time.... Once you are here...You are family!

If you fly into Newark Airport (EWR) and staying at least 7 days,  Book an UBER or Lyft taxi and send photo of bill for refund (Up to $10).   

Also, I love to ski ...Poconos Skiing resort is 50 minutes away.  You can learn  to Ski ,Snowboard, or just slide down the slopes here!!!

Thanks!!!

Hi  This is Mario!    

Look no further... 
We have an excellent support team for great stays  and nice places! 
We add new things  weekly...

I made it from NYC (Port Authority 8th Ave and 42 Street to Irvington with bus # 107X in 20 minutes when there is little traffic. 

Also,  We provide excellent WiFi and 2 WIFI networks at each house.

You may want to try downloading ROKU app for use on our Roku smart TVs.

We use door codes.  No keys needs.
We change codes after each guest leaves.

I'm giving you $5 off each of your first 4 Uber rides. To accept, use code 'marioc2038ue' to sign up. Enjoy! Details:  uber site  and  invite  and marioc2038ue

I'm originally from Costa Rica.   My Grand parents moved from Jamaica to  Limon, Costa Rica to work on building a railroad  to San Jose 100 years ago.
Limon and Costa Rica are very friendly places.  So, is Irvington, NJ, USA.

We love to provide excellent service and to excel in everything we do.

If we please you, tell many friends...If we miss our goal, please tell me..
:)  :)  :)

 I love to make new friends, good food, to explore new places and have fun.    
Please contact me if you are planning to explore NYC, NJ,  or Costa Rica.
 
We will have a great time.... Once you are here...You are family!

If you fly into Newark Airport (EWR) and staying at least 7 days,  Book an UBER or Lyft taxi and send photo of bill for refund (Up to $10).

neighborhood_overview:
Downtown Newark is a historic district consisting of early 20th-century towers. It contains the central business district and many art deco warehouses and offices that have been converted into residences. Newark offers a wide array of things to do.  There are parks, local and national restaurants, shopping, Museums, the Arts, Sports and a variety of other activities.

The Prudential Center, located in the heart of downtown, is home to the New Jersey Devils, other local sports teams and hosts many national concert tours. Also located in Downtown Newark are the New Jersey Museum of Art and the New Jersey Performing Arts Center.

From Craft Breweries to specialty local fare, Downtown Newark will not disappoint your hunger and thirst.

There are many events that take place on a year round basis that attracts locals and tourists alike.

If you run out of things to do in Newark, New York City is a 20 minute ride train ride away.

Historically, the area was called "Dutch Neck," "Down Neck," or simply "the Neck," due to the appearance of the curve of the Passaic River. Let me start by saying, thank you for considering our listings.

We have been to many countries and endless cities. We have travel for over 20 years, fluent on 6 languages. There's a big probability we have been to where you come from and have gone where you going next, so feel free to ask for traveling advice.

Thank you for your business and keep traveling/exploring until its your time to rest.

host_about:
Hi  This is Mario!    

Look no further... 
We have an excellent support team for great stays  and nice places! 
We add new things  weekly...

I made it from NYC (Port Authority 8th Ave and 42 Street to Irvington with bus # 107X in 20 minutes when there is little traffic. 

Also,  We provide excellent WiFi and 2 WIFI networks at each house.

You may want to try downloading ROKU app for use on our Roku smart TVs.

We use door codes.  No keys needs.
We change codes after each guest leaves.

I'm giving you $5 off each of your first 4 Uber rides. To accept, use code 'marioc2038ue' to sign up. Enjoy! Details:  uber site  and  invite  and marioc2038ue

I'm originally from Costa Rica.   My Grand parents moved from Jamaica to  Limon, Costa Rica to work on building a railroad  to San Jose 100 years ago.
Limon and Costa Rica are very friendly places.  So, is Irvington, NJ, USA.

We love to provide excellent service and to excel in everything we do.

If we please you, tell many friends...If we miss our goal, please tell me..
:)  :)  :)

 I love to make new friends, good food, to explore new places and have fun.    
Please contact me if you are planning to explore NYC, NJ,  or Costa Rica.
 
We will have a great time.... Once you are here...You are family!

If you fly into Newark Airport (EWR) and staying at least 7 days,  Book an UBER or Lyft taxi and send photo of bill for refund (Up to $10).   

Also, I love to ski ...Poconos Skiing resort is 50 minutes away.  You can learn  to Ski ,Snowboard, or just slide down the slopes here!!!

Thanks!!!

neighborhood_overview:
Downtown Newark is a historic district consisting of early 20th-century towers. It contains the central business district and many art deco warehouses and offices that have been converted into residences. Newark offers a wide array of things to do.  There are parks, local and national restaurants, shopping, Museums, the Arts, Sports and a variety of other activities.

The Prudential Center, located in the heart of downtown, is home to the New Jersey Devils, other local sports teams and hosts many national concert tours. Also located in Downtown Newark are the New Jersey Museum of Art and the New Jersey Performing Arts Center.

From Craft Breweries to specialty local fare, Downtown Newark will not disappoint your hunger and thirst.

There are many events that take place on a year round basis that attracts locals and tourists alike.

If you run out of things to do in Newark, New York City is a 20 minute ride train ride away.

Newark is the Garden State’s largest metropolis and is located just 8 short miles from Manhattan. Air, water, roadway, railway, bike path, footbridge and subway, Newark offers every manner of transportation imaginable, providing access that’s unbelievable.

The transportation in the Roseville neighborhood is super convenient! After taking the light rail to Newark Penn Station 2 blocks away, its only a 20 minute commute to Midtown, NYC by train.

For entertainment, the New Jersey Performing Arts Center (NJPAC). Take on the largest premium outlet mall in the state, The Outlet Collection, Jersey Gardens, welcoming over 18 million visitors a year. Other activities include the Newark Museum; NHL New Jersey Devils; and NCAA Seton Hall Men’s Basketball that you can watch close by at the Prudential Center.

neighborhood_overview:
Downtown Newark is a historic district consisting of early 20th-century towers. It contains the central business district and many art deco warehouses and offices that have been converted into residences. Newark offers a wide array of things to do.  There are parks, local and national restaurants, shopping, Museums, the Arts, Sports and a variety of other activities.

The Prudential Center, located in the heart of downtown, is home to the New Jersey Devils, other local sports teams and hosts many national concert tours. Also located in Downtown Newark are the New Jersey Museum of Art and the New Jersey Performing Arts Center.

From Craft Breweries to specialty local fare, Downtown Newark will not disappoint your hunger and thirst.

There are many events that take place on a year round basis that attracts locals and tourists alike.

If you run out of things to do in Newark, New York City is a 20 minute ride train ride away.

host_about:
Hi there! I'm Shawn, and I'm excited to introduce myself to you. With years of experience as a licensed refrigeration technician and now as an Airbnb host, I'm passionate about providing exceptional customer service and making sure my guests have an unforgettable stay. My wife and I are both New York transplants who have fallen in love with the vibrant city of Newark and we're thrilled to share our insider knowledge and tips with visitors from around the world.

Travel is my true passion, and I've been lucky enough to explore some incredible destinations. From the bustling streets of Tokyo to the serene beaches of Bali, each trip has been an opportunity to learn, grow, and connect with people from all walks of life. Now, as a host, I'm excited to welcome the world to my doorstep and offer a unique perspective on this amazing city.

Whether you're a first-time traveler or a seasoned adventurer, I'm here to make sure your stay is nothing short of exceptional. So, if you're looking for a warm and welcoming host who is dedicated to providing the very best in customer service, then look no further than me, Shawn. Thank you for considering my home for your next adventure, and I can't wait to see what incredible experiences we can create together!

neighborhood_overview:
Newark is the Garden State’s largest metropolis and is located just 8 short miles from Manhattan. Air, water, roadway, railway, bike path, footbridge and subway, Newark offers every manner of transportation imaginable, providing access that’s unbelievable.

The transportation in the Roseville neighborhood is super convenient! After taking the light rail to Newark Penn Station 2 blocks away, its only a 20 minute commute to Midtown, NYC by train.

For entertainment, the New Jersey Performing Arts Center (NJPAC). host_about:
Hi  This is Mario!    

Look no further... 
We have an excellent support team for great stays  and nice places! 
We add new things  weekly...

I made it from NYC (Port Authority 8th Ave and 42 Street to Irvington with bus # 107X in 20 minutes when there is little traffic. 

Also,  We provide excellent WiFi and 2 WIFI networks at each house.

You may want to try downloading ROKU app for use on our Roku smart TVs.

We use door codes.  No keys needs.
We change codes after each guest leaves.

I'm giving you $5 off each of your first 4 Uber rides. To accept, use code 'marioc2038ue' to sign up. Enjoy! Details:  uber site  and  invite  and marioc2038ue

I'm originally from Costa Rica.   My Grand parents moved from Jamaica to  Limon, Costa Rica to work on building a railroad  to San Jose 100 years ago.
Limon and Costa Rica are very friendly places.  So, is Irvington, NJ, USA.

We love to provide excellent service and to excel in everything we do.

If we please you, tell many friends...If we miss our goal, please tell me..
:)  :)  :)

 I love to make new friends, good food, to explore new places and have fun.    
Please contact me if you are planning to explore NYC, NJ,  or Costa Rica.
 
We will have a great time.... Once you are here...You are family!

If you fly into Newark Airport (EWR) and staying at least 7 days,  Book an UBER or Lyft taxi and send photo of bill for refund (Up to $10).   

Also, I love to ski ...Poconos Skiing resort is 50 minutes away.  You can learn  to Ski ,Snowboard, or just slide down the slopes here!!!

Thanks!!!

host_about:
Hi  This is Mario!    

Look no further... 
We have an excellent support team for great stays  and nice places! 
We add new things  weekly...

I made it from NYC (Port Authority 8th Ave and 42 Street to Irvington with bus # 107X in 20 minutes when there is little traffic. 

Also,  We provide excellent WiFi and 2 WIFI networks at each house.

You may want to try downloading ROKU app for use on our Roku smart TVs.

We use door codes.  No keys needs.
We change codes after each guest leaves.

I'm giving you $5 off each of your first 4 Uber rides. To accept, use code 'marioc2038ue' to sign up. Enjoy! Details:  uber site  and  invite  and marioc2038ue

I'm originally from Costa Rica.   My Grand parents moved from Jamaica to  Limon, Costa Rica to work on building a railroad  to San Jose 100 years ago.
Limon and Costa Rica are very friendly places.  So, is Irvington, NJ, USA.

We love to provide excellent service and to excel in everything we do.

If we please you, tell many friends...If we miss our goal, please tell me..
:)  :)  :)

 I love to make new friends, good food, to explore new places and have fun.    
Please contact me if you are planning to explore NYC, NJ,  or Costa Rica.
 
We will have a great time.... Once you are here...You are family!

If you fly into Newark Airport (EWR) and staying at least 7 days,  Book an UBER or Lyft taxi and send photo of bill for refund (Up to $10).   

Also, I love to ski ...Poconos Skiing resort is 50 minutes away.  You can learn  to Ski ,Snowboard, or just slide down the slopes here!!!

Thanks!!!

neighborhood_overview:
The suite is located in the Weequahic neighborhood of Newark, NJ.

•》Just a short drive from Newark Penn Station, Prudential Center, NJ Performing Arts Center, MetLife Stadium, Nickolodean at American Dream Mall, art and museums downtown.

•》Located less than two blocks from Weequahic Park, home to 311 acres of lush green space.

• 》Weequahic Park was designed by Olmstead, known for designing some of the world’s most famous parks that includes NYC’s Central Park and Brooklyn’s Prospect Park.

•》The park has the world’s longest resilient-surfaced (100% recycled rubber) track which wraps around a beautiful 80 acre lake, with fountain and 18 hole golf course.

•》Newark, NJ is rich in history, home to the state’s largest museum and the largest port on the east coast.

Defina helps to sculpt the NYC skyline for a living. Essentially, she puts up the steel structure of buildings & bridges. This has created in her, a fixation on city skylines across the world!

From Defina and the myCitySuite team, we welcome you to create memories with purpose and experience travel with style!

neighborhood_overview:
The apartment is nestled in the lovely Ironbound within walking distance to Downtown Newark. Its well-connected location allows you to quickly venture into NYC over the Hudson Bridge and Jersey City.

This unique and vibrant area is truly a hidden gem that offers a diverse mix of cultures, cuisines, and experiences that you're sure to fall in love with. Allow me to share some of the highlights of Ironbound that make it such a special place:

One of the things that sets Ironbound apart is its Portuguese heritage, which is evident in the neighborhood's many Portuguese restaurants, bakeries, and cultural events. If you're a foodie, you're in for a treat! Ironbound is known for its delicious seafood, grilled meats, and pastries, which you can sample at iconic eateries like Fernandes Steakhouse, Iberia Peninsula, and Teixeira's Bakery. neighborhood_overview:
Did you know that Newark is the 3rd oldest city in the nation? Established in 1666, Newark is a hidden gem with rich history!

Like many inner cities it is one going through gentrification and regeneration. Although not Beverly Hills, the neighborhoods are filled with friendly families and communities thriving.

I've lived here for 3 years and can honestly say that I've never had a problem. Newark continues to become popular as migraters enjoy the spacious atmosphere while being close to New York If you get tired of Jersey's scenic views then New York is always a 40 minute drive away (depending on traffic) to experience the city.
host_about:
Hi my name is Genesis, i manage short term rentals in Newark with my family. On my free time i enjoy hiking, discovering new food spots, site seeing, and traveling.

As a Newark native, I’m passionate about this historic city and appreciate anyone who decides to stop by and show our town some love.

host_about:
Hi  This is Mario!    

Look no further... 
We have an excellent support team for great stays  and nice places! 
We add new things  weekly...

I made it from NYC (Port Authority 8th Ave and 42 Street to Irvington with bus # 107X in 20 minutes when there is little traffic. 

Also,  We provide excellent WiFi and 2 WIFI networks at each house.

You may want to try downloading ROKU app for use on our Roku smart TVs.

We use door codes.  No keys needs.
We change codes after each guest leaves.

I'm giving you $5 off each of your first 4 Uber rides. To accept, use code 'marioc2038ue' to sign up. Enjoy! Details:  uber site  and  invite  and marioc2038ue

I'm originally from Costa Rica.   My Grand parents moved from Jamaica to  Limon, Costa Rica to work on building a railroad  to San Jose 100 years ago.
Limon and Costa Rica are very friendly places.  So, is Irvington, NJ, USA.

We love to provide excellent service and to excel in everything we do.

If we please you, tell many friends...If we miss our goal, please tell me..
:)  :)  :)

 I love to make new friends, good food, to explore new places and have fun.    
Please contact me if you are planning to explore NYC, NJ,  or Costa Rica.
 
We will have a great time.... Once you are here...You are family!

If you fly into Newark Airport (EWR) and staying at least 7 days,  Book an UBER or Lyft taxi and send photo of bill for refund (Up to $10).   

Also, I love to ski ...Poconos Skiing resort is 50 minutes away.  You can learn  to Ski ,Snowboard, or just slide down the slopes here!!!

Thanks!!!

neighborhood_overview:
Downtown Newark is a historic district consisting of early 20th-century towers. It contains the central business district and many art deco warehouses and offices that have been converted into residences. Newark offers a wide array of things to do.  There are parks, local and national restaurants, shopping, Museums, the Arts, Sports and a variety of other activities.

The Prudential Center, located in the heart of downtown, is home to the New Jersey Devils, other local sports teams and hosts many national concert tours. Also located in Downtown Newark are the New Jersey Museum of Art and the New Jersey Performing Arts Center.

From Craft Breweries to specialty local fare, Downtown Newark will not disappoint your hunger and thirst.

There are many events that take place on a year round basis that attracts locals and tourists alike.

If you run out of things to do in Newark, New York City is a 20 minute ride train ride away.

These newly renovated one, two, and three-bedroom apartments are an alternative to cramped downtown hotels, with the additional convenience of having the ability to be customized to most guest needs (contact management office directly for options)  Check-in and check-out are handled online with no in-person interaction and each apartment is cleaned and sanitized before your stay. neighborhood_overview:
Downtown Newark is a historic district consisting of early 20th-century towers. It contains the central business district and many art deco warehouses and offices that have been converted into residences. Newark offers a wide array of things to do.  There are parks, local and national restaurants, shopping, Museums, the Arts, Sports and a variety of other activities.

The Prudential Center, located in the heart of downtown, is home to the New Jersey Devils, other local sports teams and hosts many national concert tours. Also located in Downtown Newark are the New Jersey Museum of Art and the New Jersey Performing Arts Center.

From Craft Breweries to specialty local fare, Downtown Newark will not disappoint your hunger and thirst.

There are many events that take place on a year round basis that attracts locals and tourists alike.

If you run out of things to do in Newark, New York City is a 20 minute ride train ride away.

neighborhood_overview:
One of the premier cultural institutions in Newark is the Newark Museum of Art. It stands as one of the most comprehensive museums in the state, including a large collection of some 30,000 pieces of world-class Chinese, Japanese, Korean, Southeast Asian, Oceanic, and Tibetan art. The true star of the show is the Tibetan Buddhist altar – consecrated in 1990 by His Holiness the Fourteenth Dalai Lama himself. In addition, the museum boasts a planetarium, where you can explore the myths and legends of one of the most visible constellations in our night sky.
Another must-see destination in Newark is the Prudential Center. This state-of-the-art arena is home to the New Jersey Devils professional hockey team and also hosts a wide array of concerts and events – with big names such as John Mayer, Carrie Underwood, Jeff Dunham and many more!

The true star of the show is the Tibetan Buddhist altar – consecrated in 1990 by His Holiness the Fourteenth Dalai Lama himself. In addition, the museum boasts a planetarium, where you can explore the myths and legends of one of the most visible constellations in our night sky.

Another must-see destination in Newark is the Prudential Center. This state-of-the-art arena is home to the New Jersey Devils professional hockey team and also hosts a wide array of concerts and events – with big names such as John Mayer, Carrie Underwood, Jeff Dunham and many more!

Shops & restaurants close by. Perfect for business & leisure travelers. The perfect home away from home.

Apartment Includes:

➝ Free Parking
➝ Secure Bldg w/ Elevator
➝ 2 Comfy Queen Beds
➝ Full Kitchen
➝ Smart TV
➝ Comfy Pullout Sofa
➝ Laundry Room
➝ Fast Wi-Fi

See more comforts below!

The space
Apartment has spacious bedrooms including a walk-in closet in the Master Bedroom. Includes two full bathrooms & laundry room.

The apartment is thoroughly cleaned and sanitized between each stay by a professional cleaning team using Airbnb's 5 step enhanced cleaning process.

Enjoy FREE access to the 24/7 gym, lounge and game room available on the lower level of the building AKA Leve

Located withing a 5 minute walk of Newark’s Prudential Center and just a few minutes from the Newark Performing Arts center, this is the perfect location for any sports and concert enthusiasts. Also perfect for those travelers looking to visit NYC, which is a short 25 minute train ride away or a 40 minute drive.

Also located about a 10 min drive from Newark Liberty International (EWR) Airport.

name: Home in Newark · 1 bedroom · 1 bed · 1 private bath
description:
Welcome to your peaceful and quiet stay. The bedroom has a double bed, both neat and spacious with a neat and clean bathroom. Wind down with luxury sheets and high end amenities.

A 7 min drive or train ride to Penn Station and 14 min drive to EWR.

Area transportation is convenient. We are located 2 blocks from the Park Ave Train Station; 1 block from Dunkin Donuts, KFC, Dominican restaurant, laundromat, cleaners, and 2 delis; and 5 min walk to grocery.

The space
A clean and peaceful space to work, study, read in a brand new historic home! Explore the neighborhood and the famous Branch Brook Park designed by Central Park architect, William Olmsted.

The bed features a premium full sized mattress and the room has a dress rack for clothes and storage.

Please note: this is a room with ONLY a full sized bed and private bathroom like a hotel room. There is no fridge, microwave or place to store food. This space is perfect for
neighborhood_overview:
Newark is the Garden State’s largest metropolis and is located just 8 short miles from Manhattan. Air, water, roadway, railway, bike path, footbridge and subway, Newark offers every manner of transportation imaginable, providing access that’s unbelievable.

The transportation in the Roseville neighborhood is super convenient! After taking the light rail to Newark Penn Station 2 blocks away, its only a 20 minute commute to Midtown, NYC by train.

For entertainment, the New Jersey Performing Arts Center (NJPAC). Take on the largest premium outlet mall in the state, The Outlet Collection, Jersey Gardens, welcoming over 18 million visitors a year. Other activities include the Newark Museum; NHL New Jersey Devils; and NCAA Seton Hall Men’s Basketball that you can watch close by at the Prudential Center.

If you visit in the spring, experience the largest collection of cherry blossoms in the nation. Branch Brook Park blossoms with over 4,300 cherry trees, and h
host_about: You will find these Airbnbs to be bright, airy, and peaceful places for contemplation, studying, reading, working, and creating positive energy. There are lots of public transportation close by (trains and buses) as well as places to grab a bite. Don't hesitate to reach out: we look forward to hearing from you and hosting you!

It's a bustling area with a rich cultural scene and a diverse range of attractions. Here's a neighborhood description to give you a glimpse of what to expect when staying in Downtown Newark through an Airbnb lens:

Attractions: Downtown Newark is home to several must-visit attractions that are within walking distance or a short commute from your Airbnb. The New Jersey Performing Arts Center (NJPAC) is a world-class venue hosting concerts, ballets, and theater performances. The Newark Museum is another cultural gem, featuring a diverse collection of art, science exhibits, and a planetarium. If you're a sports enthusiast, the Prudential Center is a state-of-the-art arena hosting hockey games, concerts, and other events.

neighborhood_overview:
University Heights is a vibrant and diverse neighborhood located in the heart of Newark, New Jersey. As the name suggests, it is home to several major universities, including Rutgers University, New Jersey Institute of Technology, and Essex County College. The neighborhood has a lively atmosphere with many young students and professionals.

In addition to the universities, University Heights is also home to several museums, such as the Newark Museum, the New Jersey Historical Society, and the Institute of Jazz Studies. The neighborhood is also known for its beautiful parks, including Branch Brook Park, which boasts the largest collection of cherry blossom trees in the United States.

University Heights is a foodie's paradise, with a wide variety of restaurants serving cuisines from all over the world. From Mexican street food to Italian delicacies, there is something for everyone.

host_about:
Hello! 

I'm a proud New Yorker who has had the privilege of being shaped by the rich cultural tapestry that my heritage offers. My parents come from Egypt and the Dominican Republic, two countries with distinct cultures that have come together in a beautiful fusion.

Growing up in New York, I was exposed to a myriad of cultures, languages, and traditions. From the festivals and parades of the Caribbean and Latin America to the art and music of West Africa and South Asia, New York provided a glimpse into the world without ever leaving the city limits.

My Egyptian culture is deeply rooted in history, art, and religion. From the Pyramids of Giza to the cuisine with fragrant spices, herbs, and hearty dishes such as koshari, ful medames, and molokhia. Family is at the center of Egyptian culture, and gatherings are often filled with music, storytelling, and lively conversations.

The Dominican Republic, on the other hand, is known for its vibrant music, dance, and joyful celebrations. Merengue and bachata are a reflection of our spirit of rhythm and passion. The cuisine is a fusion of African, Spanish, and indigenous influences, with dishes such as mangu, sancocho, and chicharrón.

Growing up with these two rich cultures has given me a unique perspective on the world and a deep appreciation for diversity. I've been fortunate to experience the beauty of both Egyptian and Dominican cultures firsthand, from the traditional dances and music to the delicious cuisine and warm hospitality. These cultural influences, combined with the diversity of New York, have inspired me to explore other cultures and learn about their traditions and customs.

As I continue to travel and explore the world, I carry with me the richness and diversity of my heritage and the vibrancy of New York. I'm proud to share my cultural background with others, and I'm grateful for the opportunities that I've had to learn, grow, and connect with people from all over the world.

neighborhood_overview:
University Heights is a vibrant and diverse neighborhood located in the heart of Newark, New Jersey. As the name suggests, it is home to several major universities, including Rutgers University, New Jersey Institute of Technology, and Essex County College. The neighborhood has a lively atmosphere with many young students and professionals.

In addition to the universities, University Heights is also home to several museums, such as the Newark Museum, the New Jersey Historical Society, and the Institute of Jazz Studies. The neighborhood is also known for its beautiful parks, including Branch Brook Park, which boasts the largest collection of cherry blossom trees in the United States.

University Heights is a foodie's paradise, with a wide variety of restaurants serving cuisines from all over the world. From Mexican street food to Italian delicacies, there is something for everyone.

host_about:
Hello! 

I'm a proud New Yorker who has had the privilege of being shaped by the rich cultural tapestry that my heritage offers. My parents come from Egypt and the Dominican Republic, two countries with distinct cultures that have come together in a beautiful fusion.

Growing up in New York, I was exposed to a myriad of cultures, languages, and traditions. From the festivals and parades of the Caribbean and Latin America to the art and music of West Africa and South Asia, New York provided a glimpse into the world without ever leaving the city limits.

My Egyptian culture is deeply rooted in history, art, and religion. From the Pyramids of Giza to the cuisine with fragrant spices, herbs, and hearty dishes such as koshari, ful medames, and molokhia. Family is at the center of Egyptian culture, and gatherings are often filled with music, storytelling, and lively conversations.

The Dominican Republic, on the other hand, is known for its vibrant music, dance, and joyful celebrations. Merengue and bachata are a reflection of our spirit of rhythm and passion. The cuisine is a fusion of African, Spanish, and indigenous influences, with dishes such as mangu, sancocho, and chicharrón.

Growing up with these two rich cultures has given me a unique perspective on the world and a deep appreciation for diversity. I've been fortunate to experience the beauty of both Egyptian and Dominican cultures firsthand, from the traditional dances and music to the delicious cuisine and warm hospitality. These cultural influences, combined with the diversity of New York, have inspired me to explore other cultures and learn about their traditions and customs.

As I continue to travel and explore the world, I carry with me the richness and diversity of my heritage and the vibrancy of New York. I'm proud to share my cultural background with others, and I'm grateful for the opportunities that I've had to learn, grow, and connect with people from all over the world.

neighborhood_overview:
Newark is the Garden State’s largest metropolis and is located just 8 short miles from Manhattan. Air, water, roadway, railway, bike path, footbridge and subway, Newark offers every manner of transportation imaginable, providing access that’s unbelievable.

The transportation in the Roseville neighborhood is super convenient! After taking the light rail to Newark Penn Station 2 blocks away, its only a 20 minute commute to Midtown, NYC by train.

For entertainment, the New Jersey Performing Arts Center (NJPAC). Take on the largest premium outlet mall in the state, The Outlet Collection, Jersey Gardens, welcoming over 18 million visitors a year. Other activities include the Newark Museum; NHL New Jersey Devils; and NCAA Seton Hall Men’s Basketball that you can watch close by at the Prudential Center.

Newark is the Garden State’s largest metropolis and is located just 8 short miles from Manhattan. Air, water, roadway, railway, bike path, footbridge and subway, Newark offers every manner of transportation imaginable, providing access that’s unbelievable.

The transportation in the Roseville neighborhood is super convenient! After taking the light rail to Newark Penn Station 2 blocks away, its only a 20 minute commute to Midtown, NYC by train.

For entertainment, the New Jersey Performing Arts Center (NJPAC). Take on the largest premium outlet mall in the state, The Outlet Collection, Jersey Gardens, welcoming over 18 million visitors a year. Other activities include the Newark Museum; NHL New Jersey Devils; and NCAA Seton Hall Men’s Basketball that you can watch close by at the Prudential Center.

neighborhood_overview:
University Heights is a vibrant and diverse neighborhood located in the heart of Newark, New Jersey. As the name suggests, it is home to several major universities, including Rutgers University, New Jersey Institute of Technology, and Essex County College. The neighborhood has a lively atmosphere with many young students and professionals.

In addition to the universities, University Heights is also home to several museums, such as the Newark Museum, the New Jersey Historical Society, and the Institute of Jazz Studies. The neighborhood is also known for its beautiful parks, including Branch Brook Park, which boasts the largest collection of cherry blossom trees in the United States.

University Heights is a foodie's paradise, with a wide variety of restaurants serving cuisines from all over the world. From Mexican street food to Italian delicacies, there is something for everyone.

The neighborhood is well-connected with public transportation, making it ea
host_about:
Hello! 

I'm a proud New Yorker who has had the privilege of being shaped by the rich cultural tapestry that my heritage offers. My parents come from Egypt and the Dominican Republic, two countries with distinct cultures that have come together in a beautiful fusion.

Growing up in New York, I was exposed to a myriad of cultures, languages, and traditions. From the festivals and parades of the Caribbean and Latin America to the art and music of West Africa and South Asia, New York provided a glimpse into the world without ever leaving the city limits.

My Egyptian culture is deeply rooted in history, art, and religion. From the Pyramids of Giza to the cuisine with fragrant spices, herbs, and hearty dishes such as koshari, ful medames, and molokhia. Family is at the center of Egyptian culture, and gatherings are often filled with music, storytelling, and lively conversations.

The Dominican Republic, on the other hand, is known for its vibrant music, dance, and joyful celebrations. Merengue and bachata are a reflection of our spirit of rhythm and passion. The cuisine is a fusion of African, Spanish, and indigenous influences, with dishes such as mangu, sancocho, and chicharrón.

Growing up with these two rich cultures has given me a unique perspective on the world and a deep appreciation for diversity. I've been fortunate to experience the beauty of both Egyptian and Dominican cultures firsthand, from the traditional dances and music to the delicious cuisine and warm hospitality. These cultural influences, combined with the diversity of New York, have inspired me to explore other cultures and learn about their traditions and customs.

As I continue to travel and explore the world, I carry with me the richness and diversity of my heritage and the vibrancy of New York. I'm proud to share my cultural background with others, and I'm grateful for the opportunities that I've had to learn, grow, and connect with people from all over the world.

neighborhood_overview:
Newark is the Garden State’s largest metropolis and is located just 8 short miles from Manhattan. Air, water, roadway, railway, bike path, footbridge and subway, Newark offers every manner of transportation imaginable, providing access that’s unbelievable.

The transportation in the Roseville neighborhood is super convenient! After taking the light rail to Newark Penn Station 2 blocks away, its only a 20 minute commute to Midtown, NYC by train.

For entertainment, the New Jersey Performing Arts Center (NJPAC). Take on the largest premium outlet mall in the state, The Outlet Collection, Jersey Gardens, welcoming over 18 million visitors a year. Other activities include the Newark Museum; NHL New Jersey Devils; and NCAA Seton Hall Men’s Basketball that you can watch close by at the Prudential Center.

If you visit in the spring, experience the largest collection of cherry blossoms in the nation. Branch Brook Park blossoms with over 4,300 cherry trees, and h
